{
  "texts": [
    "Typically, the clinical diagnosis of vitiligo relies on a combination of physical examination, dermoscopy, and wood lamp examination.",
    "There is no single diagnostic test that conclusively confirms vitiligo, which requires the involvement of a dermatologist with expertise in vitiligo.",
    "Unfortunately, there is a shortage of dermatologists and an unequal distribution of medical resources.",
    "In some remote areas, even non-dermatologists have to undertake the diagnosis and treatment of vitiligo due to medical resource constraints, despite their limited knowledge and training in this field.",
    "Although dermatology textbooks can be used as reference material, accurate identification and diagnosis is still the main challenge for these laypersons."
  ]
}